# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
# Saturn Environment Configuration — Runner VM
# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
#
# Copy this file to the Saturn Runner VM:
#   scp saturn.env.runner saturn@your-runner:/home/saturn/saturn/saturn.env
#
# Then edit with your actual values:
#   ssh saturn@your-runner
#   nano /home/saturn/saturn/saturn.env
#
# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# CODING ENGINE
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# Choose your AI coding engine:
#   cursor  — Cursor Agent CLI (recommended, very capable)
#   goose   — Goose CLI (open-source by Block, great for Scala/Java repos)
LLM_PROVIDER=cursor

# ── Cursor (if LLM_PROVIDER=cursor) ──
# Path to Cursor Agent CLI (installed via: curl https://cursor.com/install -fsS | bash)
CURSOR_CLI_PATH=/home/saturn/.local/bin/agent

# Timeout for Cursor invocations (10 minutes)
CURSOR_TIMEOUT_SECONDS=600

# ── Goose (if LLM_PROVIDER=goose) ──
# Install: curl -fsSL https://github.com/block/goose/releases/latest/download/goose-installer.sh | bash
GOOSE_CLI_PATH=goose

# Timeout for Goose invocations (10 minutes)
GOOSE_TIMEOUT_SECONDS=600

# Model provider for Goose (anthropic, openai, ollama, etc.)
GOOSE_PROVIDER=anthropic

# Specific model for Goose (e.g. claude-3-5-sonnet-20241022, gpt-4o)
GOOSE_MODEL=claude-3-5-sonnet-20241022

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# TARGET REPOSITORY (REQUIRED)
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# The zdpas repository URL
# ⚠️  CHANGE THIS to your actual repo URL
REPO_URL=https://gitlab.zoho.com/zdpas/zdpas.git

# Where Saturn stores the bare clone (persistent across tasks)
REPO_LOCAL_PATH=/data/saturn/repo

# Where Saturn creates worktrees (one per task, cleaned up after)
WORKTREE_BASE_DIR=/data/saturn/tasks

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# GITLAB CONFIGURATION (REQUIRED)
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# GitLab instance URL
# ⚠️  CHANGE THIS to your GitLab URL
GITLAB_URL=https://gitlab.zoho.com

# GitLab Personal Access Token with 'api' scope
# Generate at: GitLab → User Settings → Access Tokens
# ⚠️  CHANGE THIS to your actual token
GITLAB_TOKEN=glpat-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# GitLab Project ID (numeric) or path (group/project)
# Find at: Project → Settings → General → Project ID
# ⚠️  CHANGE THIS to your project ID
GITLAB_PROJECT_ID=12345

# Default branch name
#GITLAB_DEFAULT_BRANCH=master

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# ZOHO CLIQ INTEGRATION (OPTIONAL)
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# Bot unique name (from Cliq Admin → Bots → Your Bot)
CLIQ_BOT_UNIQUE_NAME=saturnbot

# Bot ZAPI Key (from Cliq Admin → Bots → Your Bot → API → ZAPI Key)
# ⚠️  CHANGE THIS to your actual ZAPI key
CLIQ_BOT_ZAPIKEY=1001.xxxxxxxxxxxx.xxxxxxxxxxxx

# Channel API URL for posting messages
CLIQ_BOT_API_URL=https://cliq.zoho.in/api/v2/channelsbyname/saturn-tasks/message

# Channel unique name
CLIQ_CHANNEL_UNIQUE_NAME=saturn-tasks

# Chat ID for thread replies (optional)
CLIQ_CHAT_ID=

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# DPAAS-SPECIFIC SETTINGS
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# Saturn runs on a dedicated VM and owns DPAAS_HOME entirely.
# At startup Saturn extracts the tar files into DPAAS_HOME ONCE.
# No GitLab runner required; no pre-existing DPAAS_HOME needed.

# Target directory for DPAAS runtime (jars, resources, conf).
# Saturn creates it on first startup if absent.
DPAAS_HOME=/opt/dpaas

# Directory containing datastore.json (provided by CI/CD, not in the tars).
# datastore.json is copied into DPAAS_HOME/zdpas/spark/resources/ at startup.
BUILD_FILE_HOME=/home/saturn/build-files

# ── DPAAS Source Tars ──
# Paths to the tar files that Saturn extracts into DPAAS_HOME at startup.
# Paths can be absolute or relative to the Saturn working directory.
DPAAS_SOURCE_TAR=build/ZDPAS/output/dpaas.tar.gz
DPAAS_TEST_TAR=build/ZDPAS/output/dpaas_test.tar.gz

# Set to true to force re-extraction on next startup.
# Use when new jars or resources have been added to the tars.
# DPAAS_FORCE_REINIT=false

# ── Saturn MCP Server (Toolshed — Layer 2, Stripe Minions pattern) ──
# Auto-registered in ~/.config/goose/config.yaml as a Goose extension.
# Provides fast ZDPAS tools: compile_quick (5–30 s), run_module_tests, search_code.
MCP_ENABLED=true

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# SERVER SETTINGS
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# Server bind address (0.0.0.0 = all interfaces)
SERVER_HOST=0.0.0.0

# Server port
SERVER_PORT=8000

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# AGENT LIMITS
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# Maximum iterations in the agent loop (prevents infinite loops)
MAX_LOOP_ITERATIONS=20

# LLM thinking budget (for legacy mode)
THINKING_BUDGET_TOKENS=10000

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# LEGACY LLM SETTINGS (only if LLM_PROVIDER != cursor)
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# Ollama (local LLM)
OLLAMA_BASE_URL=http://localhost:11434
OLLAMA_MODEL=qwen2.5:7b

# Anthropic (cloud LLM) — requires API key
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

